HEADWORD: choanocyte
<hw>cho"a*no*cyte`</hw> <pr>(k⟦omac⟧"⟦adot⟧*n⟦osl⟧*s⟦imac⟧t`;
k⟦omac⟧*⟦acr⟧n"⟦osl⟧*s⟦imac⟧t`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>choa`nh</grk> funnel + <ets>-cyte</ets>.]</ety> <def>any of the
flagellated cells in sponges having a collar of cytoplasm around base of
the flagellum; they maintain a flow of water through the body.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> collar cell.</syn>⟦br⟧
